title: "Perf: pm context / pm next hot path ~700ms on an ~850-item tracker"
description: "From 2026-07-02 audit (Lane D, pm-3l76): node startup is ~60ms, but pm context --limit 5 and pm next take ~700ms warm on this repo (857 items); list-open ~430ms, get ~335ms. Dominant cost is full-corpus load + actionability scan. Candidates: reuse/extend the front-matter cache on the context/next path, lazy-load bodies, avoid re-parsing closed items for ready-leaf computation. Target: common reads under ~300ms."
